'''Impressionist Masters''' is a special exhibition at the [[Musée d'Orsay]] tracing the development of light and colour in French Impressionism. Drawing on the museum's deep holdings of late 19th-century painting, it charts the movement's break with academic conventions.

Featured artists include [[Claude Monet]] and [[Vincent van Gogh]], shown alongside their contemporaries to track how Impressionist techniques were absorbed and reinterpreted in the decades that followed.
